The vocal processing could use some refinement, especially in the ad-libs during the outro. Experiment with different EQ settings and vocal effects to make them stand out without overpowering the main vocals.

The hi-hats in the drum pattern sound a bit dull and repetitive. Adding some variation in velocity and incorporating different hi-hat samples or patterns can make the rhythm more dynamic and engaging.
The overall mix lacks depth and dimension, particularly in the mid-range frequencies.
Try using subtle reverb and delay effects on certain elements to create a sense of space and atmosphere, enhancing the overall sonic landscape of the track.

The vocal harmonies in the bridge section could be more pronounced to add depth and richness to the arrangement. Consider doubling the vocal tracks or adding subtle vocal effects to enhance their impact.
The synth melodies in the verses feel a bit repetitive. Adding variation in note lengths or introducing new melodic elements can keep the listener engaged and prevent the song from feeling stagnant.

The bassline in the chorus lacks definition and could benefit from compression or saturation to add warmth and presence. Experimenting with different bass sound presets or layering techniques can help achieve a more impactful low-end.

The transition between the verse and chorus sections feels abrupt. Incorporating a subtle fill or riser leading into the chorus can smooth out the transition and create a more cohesive flow between the different parts of the song.
The vocal delivery feels disconnected from the instrumental. Adding subtle vocal effects like reverb or delay can help blend the vocals with the music, creating a more cohesive sonic atmosphere.
The guitar tone lacks depth and could benefit from layering or re-amping to achieve a fuller sound. Experimenting with different amp settings or adding modulation effects can add texture.
The bassline in "Heladito" could be more prominent to drive the groove forward. Adding compression and saturation can bring out its warmth and energy, enhancing the overall rhythm of the track
The vocals could benefit from a touch of modulation effects like chorus or flanger to add depth and character. This would complement the dreamy atmosphere of the song and make the vocals stand out.

Incorporating subtle background textures or atmospheric sounds could enrich the sonic landscape of "Heladito", creating a more immersive listening experience. Experimenting with ambient synths or field recordings can add depth and intrigue to the production.
